The White House is announcing new commitments and initiatives to support inclusive entrepreneurship and innovation in the United States. These include expanding the Small Business Administration's Startup in a Day initiative to streamline the process of starting a business, adopting new expansions of the National Science Foundation's Innovation Corps (I-Corps) entrepreneurship-training program, and over 30 companies joining a new Tech Inclusion Pledge to increase diversity in the technology workforce. The goal is to tap into America's full entrepreneurial potential and promote diversity in the technology sector. Additionally, the Department of Agriculture and Department of Energy are providing funding to stimulate the development and adoption of innovative approaches and technologies. The article also highlights the 2016 Global Entrepreneurship Summit and the importance of entrepreneurship in driving economic growth and innovation.